Cool overcast weather provided the ideal setting for Mitchell House College learners to impress their trainers during the inter-house athletics that was hosted on Friday.
Mitchell House Director of Sport, Fred Romijn said that although the event had a very competitive edge, the aim was to identify talent to represent the school and no results were released.
